          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- By Authors - Natural rubidium contains about 27.8%",
                "Rb-87. At some bombarding energies the same product",
                "nucleus can therefore be formed from the two isotopes",
                "85Rb and 87Rb by different reaction channels. To",
                "avoid any complication due to the presence 87Rb, the",
                "alpha-energy range for any particular reaction channel",
                "was selected in such a way that 87Rb could not",
                "contribute significantly to the production of the",
                "nucleus of interest."
              ]
            }
          ],
